name: Aurora borealis northern lights forecast
summary: Multiple news outlets predict the Northern Lights (Aurora Borealis) will be visible across several states in the US during Thanksgiving and Black Friday due to anticipated geomagnetic storms. The aurora may be seen in areas such as Vermont, Wisconsin, New York City, and Indiana. NOAA has provided a view line map to help determine specific visibility locations. Forecasters expect the aurora to be visible in northern states, particularly those under the "Kp 5" or higher range on the geomagnetic storm scale. Enthusiasts are encouraged to check local news sources and NOAA updates for the latest information on visibility and specific viewing locations.

summary: A new chapter has opened in the decades-old mystery of D.B. Cooper, the infamous plane hijacker. name: Walmart DEI policies
summary: In recent news, Walmart has joined a growing number of major companies, including Toyota, in rolling back their Diversity, Equity, and Inclusion (DEI) policies. This move comes amid criticism from conservative groups who argue that DEI initiatives create division and unfair advantages for certain groups. Walmart's decision, as the largest private employer in the nation, has sparked debate about the role of DEI policies in corporate America. Some see the rollback as a step back from promoting diversity and inclusion, while others believe it will foster a more inclusive environment by focusing on individual merit rather than group identity.
